articles.description: Jordon Varnado scored 23 points with 13 rebounds and Troy defeated Little Rock 82-64 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Varnado leads Troy with double-double in 82-64 win

articles.description: Johnathan Stove had a career-best 28 points and Bryce Washington added 18 with 13 rebounds as Louisiana recovered from its only Sun Belt Conference loss by getting past Georgia Southern 102-91 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Louisiana recovers from only league loss, beats Ga. Southern

articles.description: Dachon Burke scored 29 points, Matty McConnell added 23 -- both career highs -- and the pair combined for seven 3-pointers as Robert Morris beat LIU Brooklyn 96-82 on Saturday to snap a four-game slide.
articles.headline: Robert Morris tops LIU Brooklyn 96-82

articles.description: Eugene German scored 28 points, the last coming on a drive with four seconds left in overtime, and Northern Illinois knocked off Mid-American Conference leader Buffalo 90-88 on Saturday.
articles.headline: German scores 28, OT winner as NIU upsets Buffalo 90-88

articles.description: Keita Bates-Diop takes the pass from Jae'Sean Tate and knocks down a 3-pointer for Ohio State.
articles.headline: Bates-Diop drills 3

images.caption: Keita Bates-Diop takes the pass from Jae'Sean Tate and knocks down a 3-pointer for Ohio State.

articles.description: Ryan Swan scored 17 points and grabbed 10 rebounds and Air Force earned a season split with New Mexico by upsetting the Lobos, 100-92 on Saturday afternoon in a Mountain West Conference battle.
articles.headline: Air Force shoots past New Mexico in 2nd half for 100-92 win

videos.description: Jeff Roberson hits a 3-pointer at the top of the key off the dish from Saben Lee for the Commodores.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Roberson swishes rainbow 3-pointer

videos.description: Matthew Fisher-Davis receives the ball from Riley LaChance and swishes a 3-pointer for the Commodores.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Fisher-Davis buries corner 3-pointer

videos.description: Daniel Giddens pumps up the Crimson Tide bench with a slam dunk in transition.
videos.headline: Alabama's Giddens rocks the rim with two-handed dunk

videos.description: Saben Lee makes a tough transition layup off the pass from Riley LaChance for the Commodores.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Lee catches and scores an acrobatic layup

videos.description: Alabama's Collin Sexton executes a stop-and-go to get through the Vanderbilt defense and scores a right-handed finger roll layup to cap an 8-0 run for the Crimson Tide.
videos.headline: Sexton freezes defender, flies to the cup

videos.description: Herb Jones uses his lengthy athleticism to track down Vanderbilt Jeff Roberson and reject him at the rim in transition.
videos.headline: Alabama's Jones with a transition block shot

videos.description: Alabama's Collin Sexton and Dazon Ingram execute the fast break beautifully with a sweet dish and finish for the Crimson Tide.
videos.headline: Sexton, Ingram combine for fast-break layup

videos.description: Jeff Roberson drives to the rim and finishes at the bucket with a right-handed layup and get an old-fashioned 3-point play.
videos.headline: Roberson finishes at the rim for and-1

videos.description: Riley LaChance hits a 3-pointer off a sweet step-back move to increase the lead for the Commodores.
videos.headline: LaChance sings the nylon song with a nasty 3-pointer

videos.description: Braxton Key and Donta Hall execute the alley-oop to perfection and get the two-handed slam jam.
videos.headline: Key, Hall connect for alley-oop slam

videos.description: Donta Hall comes over on for weak-side help and rejects the shot of Jeff Roberson for the Crimson Tide.

videos.description: Djery Baptiste emerges from a mad scramble for the ball and scores a timely layup for the Commodores.
videos.headline: Baptiste scores clutch layup late for Vanderbilt
